1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,918
Characters, actions, places, occupations, and events in this series are fictional and created for entertainment purposes only.

2
00:00:06,918 --> 00:00:10,823
They are not intended to urge or promote any behavior in the series.

3
00:00:10,823 --> 00:00:13,135
Viewer discretion is advised.

4
00:00:13,688 --> 00:00:15,811
When do people fall out of love?

5
00:00:15,811 --> 00:00:18,648
If I didn’t want to have a new start, 	 
I wouldn’t have come all the way here.

6
00:00:18,648 --> 00:00:21,281
What you need to end, it’s maybe in there.

7
00:00:22,664 --> 00:00:23,354
I found it.

8
00:00:25,248 --> 00:00:26,703
I’ll watch out for you.

9
00:00:26,703 --> 00:00:29,844
Why did you write
 “Please make Payu love me forever”?

10
00:00:29,844 --> 00:00:31,618
You often act like you don’t love me.

11
00:00:31,618 --> 00:00:32,385
Did you cut it?

12
00:00:32,959 --> 00:00:33,693
Yes.

13
00:00:33,843 --> 00:00:34,343
Cheers.

14
00:00:34,343 --> 00:00:37,103
After you cut the Ema plaque, 
does the hallucination really stop?

15
00:00:37,103 --> 00:00:40,634
I stopped seeing the hallucination 
before I cut the plaque.

16
00:00:40,634 --> 00:00:42,200
Since when did it stop?

17
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:43,443
Since I met you.

18
00:01:24,667 --> 00:01:25,995
The breakfast tastes good.

19
00:01:28,782 --> 00:01:29,607
Yes.

20
00:01:39,197 --> 00:01:40,136
I feel like…

21
00:01:41,030 --> 00:01:42,570
today’s atmosphere is strange.

22
00:01:44,527 --> 00:01:45,686
It feels like teenagers kissed 
and tried to hide it.

23
00:01:45,686 --> 00:01:46,340
No, it’s not.

24
00:01:50,830 --> 00:01:52,027
Nothing happened.

25
00:01:55,687 --> 00:01:57,841
What did she say?

26
00:01:59,096 --> 00:01:59,895
No.

27
00:02:00,342 --> 00:02:01,339
It’s nothing.

28
00:02:18,816 --> 00:02:19,919
Satsuki, I…

29
00:02:19,919 --> 00:02:20,971
Don’t say anything.

30
00:02:21,865 --> 00:02:23,284
It’s just a kiss.

31
00:02:30,199 --> 00:02:31,912
It may sound strange.

32
00:02:33,955 --> 00:02:35,920
Every time I’m with you,

33
00:02:39,388 --> 00:02:40,880
I stop seeing the hallucination.

34
00:02:46,955 --> 00:02:49,600
At first, I didn’t know why.

35
00:02:56,153 --> 00:02:57,864
Now, I think I get it.

36
00:03:05,882 --> 00:03:06,794
I’m sorry.

37
00:03:09,135 --> 00:03:12,398
You are still sad about your boyfriend.

38
00:03:14,994 --> 00:03:16,470
I shouldn’t say this.

39
00:03:20,768 --> 00:03:21,694
It’s okay.

40
00:03:23,034 --> 00:03:25,236
It doesn’t make me feel bad.

41
00:03:46,601 --> 00:03:47,460
Anyway.

42
00:03:48,141 --> 00:03:50,910
You’ve been looking for the Ema plaque 
for a few days.

43
00:03:51,187 --> 00:03:52,242
Did you find it?

44
00:03:52,710 --> 00:03:54,645
Yes, we found it.

45
00:03:54,645 --> 00:03:57,778
So there’s nothing left for him to do?

46
00:04:04,885 --> 00:04:09,590
She asked if you have nothing left to do here.

47
00:04:10,654 --> 00:04:11,180
Oh.

48
00:04:12,542 --> 00:04:14,153
Is she implicitly telling me to leave?

49
00:04:14,706 --> 00:04:15,565
No.

50
00:04:16,948 --> 00:04:18,964
She probably…

51
00:04:20,326 --> 00:04:23,278
doesn’t want you to leave.

52
00:04:25,214 --> 00:04:26,581
Oh, I see.

53
00:04:28,815 --> 00:04:31,071
Okay. Thank you.

54
00:05:32,510 --> 00:05:35,778
APOLOGY

55
00:05:38,417 --> 00:05:41,558
You can stay for another few days.

56
00:05:42,260 --> 00:05:45,830
When I have my day off, 
I’ll give you a ride to the airport.

57
00:05:48,405 --> 00:05:49,683
Don’t worry about that.

58
00:05:50,045 --> 00:05:51,419
You should hurry and go to work.

59
00:05:52,121 --> 00:05:53,934
See you after work.

60
00:05:55,466 --> 00:05:56,262
Bye.

61
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:24,500
Yes.

62
00:06:29,103 --> 00:06:29,812
Right.

63
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:45,234
Payu, do you think Satsuki is cute?

64
00:06:53,855 --> 00:06:56,517
Yes, she is cute.

65
00:07:04,730 --> 00:07:08,222
She’s been living with me for several years.

66
00:07:09,094 --> 00:07:11,077
Although she is a cheerful girl,

67
00:07:11,311 --> 00:07:12,238
when she has a problem,

68
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,342
she tends to keep it to herself.

69
00:07:21,619 --> 00:07:22,546
Yes.

70
00:07:26,121 --> 00:07:27,601
About her ex,

71
00:07:27,792 --> 00:07:30,102
we all knew that it was over.

72
00:07:30,655 --> 00:07:31,990
But she was still waiting for him.

73
00:07:33,182 --> 00:07:34,789
It must be very painful for her.

74
00:07:35,619 --> 00:07:38,838
That’s why I’m so thankful to you.

75
00:07:39,647 --> 00:07:41,724
I don’t know what happened.

76
00:07:42,618 --> 00:07:46,505
But she’s finally able to move on from him 
and be able to smile again.

77
00:08:14,591 --> 00:08:20,214
Satsuki, when she falls in love, 
she will try her best to be a good girlfriend.

78
00:08:21,648 --> 00:08:23,475
She has a strong faith in love.

79
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:26,059
I really hope that she will be happy.

80
00:08:26,676 --> 00:08:29,239
I don’t want to see her be betrayed again.

81
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,862
I don’t want to watch her 
keep waiting for him again.

82
00:08:33,305 --> 00:08:34,865
Payu, do you think the same?

83
00:08:47,779 --> 00:08:50,338
I always believed that one day

84
00:08:50,338 --> 00:08:53,480
I would move to Tokyo to live with him.

85
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:55,110
I thought we would get married.

86
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:58,435
I really believed it.

87
00:09:34,647 --> 00:09:35,325
(Hello.)

88
00:09:35,325 --> 00:09:35,825
Jab.

89
00:09:37,378 --> 00:09:38,544
I found the plaque.

90
00:09:46,077 --> 00:09:46,588
Oh.

91
00:09:47,503 --> 00:09:48,588
Are you leaving?

92
00:10:00,460 --> 00:10:01,858
Are you leaving?

93
00:10:08,261 --> 00:10:10,186
I have something 
I need to go back and take care of.

94
00:10:16,083 --> 00:10:18,769
Did you tell Satsuki that you’re leaving?

95
00:10:24,578 --> 00:10:26,353
I’ll go to see her at the restaurant 
to say goodbye.

96
00:10:30,119 --> 00:10:31,860
Do you want me to call a taxi for you?

97
00:10:35,392 --> 00:10:36,303
It’s okay.

98
00:10:36,686 --> 00:10:39,448
I have a place I want to stop by 
before I leave.

99
00:10:44,214 --> 00:10:45,815
Thank you for letting me stay here.

100
00:10:51,900 --> 00:10:52,700
Thank you.

101
00:11:13,387 --> 00:11:14,333
Auntie.

102
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:17,228
Can I hold you?

103
00:11:33,844 --> 00:11:34,726
Payu.

104
00:11:35,641 --> 00:11:39,360
Thank you for helping Satsuki 
to be able to smile again.

105
00:11:40,658 --> 00:11:41,545
Thank you.

106
00:11:42,098 --> 00:11:42,946
Thank you.

107
00:12:37,149 --> 00:12:39,550
Do you know how many times 
you broke your promise to me?

108
00:12:39,805 --> 00:12:40,569
Hey.

109
00:12:41,548 --> 00:12:43,108
Why are you so upset about it?

110
00:12:43,597 --> 00:12:44,829
I just forgot your birthday present.

111
00:12:44,829 --> 00:12:46,225
I will get you one.

112
00:12:46,395 --> 00:12:48,091
Am I important to you?

113
00:12:48,900 --> 00:12:50,389
It’s just a bouquet.

114
00:12:51,432 --> 00:12:52,496
Am I asking too much?

115
00:12:52,496 --> 00:12:53,606
Okay, okay. How about this?

116
00:12:55,308 --> 00:12:56,360
I’ll go get you one right now.

117
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:57,078
Okay?

118
00:12:58,206 --> 00:12:58,989
Forget it.

119
00:12:59,202 --> 00:13:00,398
I don’t want it anymore.

120
00:13:03,701 --> 00:13:05,464
I don’t want 
to celebrate my birthday with you anymore.

121
00:13:10,188 --> 00:13:10,969
Payu.

122
00:13:18,696 --> 00:13:19,287
I…

123
00:13:23,500 --> 00:13:24,255
I…

124
00:13:25,532 --> 00:13:26,567
I’m sorry.

125
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:28,359
It’s my fault.

126
00:13:28,359 --> 00:13:30,411
I’m really sorry.

127
00:14:11,136 --> 00:14:12,524
PLEASE MAKE PAYU LOVE ME FOREVER.

128
00:14:12,843 --> 00:14:14,404
I’m going back to Thailand today.

129
00:14:15,340 --> 00:14:17,631
Why did you suddenly decide to go back?

130
00:14:17,908 --> 00:14:21,010
Will you come back?
